  "What does it mean to be 'underwater' on a car loan?": "",
  "The vehicle has flood damage on its history report": "",
  "You owe more on the loan than the car is currently worth": "",
  "The loan has a variable interest rate that increased": "",
  "Your monthly payment exceeds your budget": "",
  "Being underwater (negative equity) means the loan balance exceeds the vehicle's market value. This commonly occurs with long-term loans and small down payments, since cars depreciate faster than the loan is paid down.": "",
  "What does 'capitalization rate' (cap rate) mean in real estate investing?": "",
  "The percentage of the purchase price required as a down payment": "",
  "The annual percentage by which a property appreciates": "",
  "The ratio of net operating income to the property's purchase price or market value": "",
  "The mortgage interest rate for investment properties": "",
  "Cap rate = NOI / Property Value. It measures the expected rate of return on a property independent of financing, allowing investors to compare properties of different sizes and prices on a common basis.": "",
  "What does 'leverage' mean in real estate?": "",
  "Using borrowed money (a mortgage) to control a larger asset, which amplifies both gains and losses": "",
  "Negotiating a lower purchase price below market value": "",
  "Flipping a property for a quick profit": "",
  "Paying entirely in cash to avoid interest": "",
  "Leverage allows you to control a large asset with a relatively small amount of your own money. A 20% down payment on a $200,000 property means $40,000 controls $200,000 in real estate, but losses are also amplified.": "",
  "What is 'gap insurance' for auto loans?": "",
  "Insurance that covers the gap between maintenance intervals": "",
  "Insurance that covers gaps in your driving history": "",
  "A warranty that fills gaps in manufacturer coverage": "",
  "Insurance that covers the difference between what you owe on the loan and the car's actual cash value if it is totaled or stolen": "",
  "GAP (Guaranteed Asset Protection) insurance pays the difference between your loan balance and the car's depreciated value if it is totaled. This is especially important when you owe more than the car is worth.": "",
