  "What does 'depreciation' mean in the context of auto loans?": "",
  "The increase in a car's value over time due to inflation": "",
  "The interest charged on an auto loan": "",
  "A tax deduction available to all car owners": "",
  "The decrease in a vehicle's market value over time due to age, wear, and mileage": "",
  "Auto depreciation is the loss of value over time. Cars typically lose 20% in the first year and about 60% over five years, which is why depreciation is a critical factor in financing decisions.": "",
  "What is the 'mortgage interest deduction'?": "",
  "A reduction in the mortgage interest rate offered by the lender": "",
  "A penalty for paying off a mortgage early": "",
  "The portion of each payment that goes toward interest rather than principal": "",
  "A tax benefit allowing homeowners to deduct mortgage interest from taxable income, reducing the effective cost of homeownership": "",
  "The mortgage interest deduction lets homeowners who itemize deductions subtract mortgage interest paid from their taxable income (on loans up to $750,000), effectively reducing the net cost of borrowing.": "",
  "What does 'net operating income' (NOI) refer to in real estate?": "",
